The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Jan. 6: The rate of inflation declined to 4.40 per cent for the week ended December 24 from 4.62 per cent in the preceding week, mainly due to cheaper food and manufactured items. It was at 6.56 per cent in the year-ago period. The wholesale price index declined by 0.2 per cent to 196.8 points despite firm fuel prices and costlier non-food items.

 Mumbai, Jan. 6: The forex reserves decreased by $6,844 million to $137 billion during the week ended December 30 against $144 billion during the preceding week. Foreign currency assets decreased by $7,191 million to $131.018 billion, according to figures released by the Reserve Bank of India.

 New Delhi, Jan. 6: Finance minister P. Chidambaram will hold pre-budget meetings for four days with various groups next week. He will meet industrialists on Monday and agriculturalists on Tuesday. Trade union leaders will call on him on Thursday, while economists will interact with him on Friday.

 Mumbai, Jan. 6: Merck Ltd will sell off its life science and analytics business to Merck Specialties, a 100 per cent subsidiary of German Merck KGAA, for a consideration of Rs 99.2 crore.

 Mumbai, Jan. 6: The government has decided to double SME credit in the next five years, finance minister P. Chidambaram said.




